element.name: N is for Nun by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: Nuns have played a huge part in Irish life, particularly as nurses. Many hospitals were started by orders, but with falling numbers of vocations, most are now run on a secular basis.
element.encoded-hints: Behind where the two walls meet

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by BlueFoxPL
Another great day for caching... found with some friends. TFTC.

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by colmyster
Last cache of the day. Nice little one. Picked up a Summer Meltdown 2008 geocoin. Let me sister drop the goodies into it.
TFTC

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by Wicca Cailín
Last cache of ten today. Was born near here so it was a nice one to end the day. In bone pen and Dorey bouncing ball. Found with Colmyster and Bluefox PL. TFTC.

2010-06-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by polorein
Found with CR nice walk.

2010-05-16T19:00:00Z : Found it by Lynjas
Nice cache after doing the 3 along the Dodder. Dropped off Mr Jiffy's Summer Meltdown coin #35. TFTC

2007-09-02T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
Followed the GPS into the wrong spot, easy to do but quickly decided it wouldn't possibly be there - not like Hezekiah to do that. And we were right, classic Hezekiah hide so we had the cache in hand in moments. Left badge and marble.
